@startuml
title BIOS setup sequence
start
:Enter BIOS after first default boot;
:Confirm CPU, 32GB RAM, SSD, pump, and fans;
:Load optimized defaults if board history is unknown;
:Confirm UEFI, TPM/fTPM, and Secure Boot availability;
:Set Windows USB as temporary boot device;
:Install Windows 11 Pro;
:Install drivers;
:Return to BIOS;
if (Default boot and drivers stable?) then (yes)
  :Enable EXPO profile;
  :Save and reboot;
  :Allow DDR5 memory training;
  :Verify DDR5-6000 profile;
else (no)
  :Keep defaults and troubleshoot first;
endif
stop
@enduml
